"2019/09/17 C03004632\n\nUnited States, Britain, and France, which also form the Standing Group of NATO, had agreed to maintain the status quo in the Middle East.\n\nFrance proposes that a solution be sought which would reconcile the interests of the Big Three and those of the Middle East countries, including Israel, and which would also enable the Middle East to defend itself.\n\nComment: The French consider the Turkish-Iraqi treaty as a cover for Iraqi designs for union with Syria, and hence a threat to France's \"special position\" of influence in Syria. the French were assured that Britain would be prepared to disclaim publicly any designs on Syria when London joins the Turkish-Iraqi treaty", "token_count": 115, "token_end_0based": 117, "token_start_0based": 3, "token_text": "2019 09 17 c03004632 united states britain and france which also form the standing group of nato had agreed to maintain the status quo in the middle east france proposes that a solution be sought which would reconcile the interests of the big three and those of the middle east countries including israel and which would also enable the middle east to defend itself comment the french consider the turkish-iraqi treaty as a cover for iraqi designs for union with syria and hence a threat to france's special position of influence in syria the french were assured that britain would be prepared to disclaim publicly any designs on syria when london joins the turkish-iraqi treaty", "unred_source_page": 6}
